Tim McGraw is scheduled to headline a Connecticut concert for the Sandy Hook Promise group on July 17 . 
  The singer is facing backlash from conservative fans who say he risks losing his career . 
  The charity was formed in response to the 2012 Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting . 
  McGraw said that he supports gun control and is a supporter of the charity . 
  Opening act Bill Currington walked away from the show after the backlash . 
 